Thanks for your notes back after we announced October 10th as the
weekend for the 2014 CM Retreat - we share your excitement!

The retreat will be hosted in San Diego this year so we'll be able to
enjoy some great weather as well as the company of friends.

Please fill out the following very quick survey so we can get a
headcount and begin planning appropriately:
https://www.surveymonkey.com/s/L32DWK6


We've received a couple of questions regarding the weekend:
- The retreat will officially kick off Friday, Oct 10 during the day,
and last until Sunday, mid-day.
- There will be a cost for attending the event - $150 in order to help
cover room and food. Once there, we hope to keep any other expenses
you'll incurr to a minimum, so you can enjoy the weekend to the
fullest.
- Scholarships will be addressed at a later date, once we are able to
confirm a budget and attendance.
- Significant others are invited - just make sure to let us know they're coming!

Thanks again, and we look forward to seeing you all in October!



2014 Planning Committee

Sam, Ernestine, Tariq, Joe, Ana, Bethany, Varun, Garrett, and Ansaf




--
Samantha A. Penabad
spenabad@gmail.com | (908) 962-7452

Thanks for your notes back after we announced October 10th as the
weekend for the 2014 CM Retreat - we share your excitement!

The retreat will be hosted in San Diego this year so we'll be able to
enjoy some great weather as well as the company of friends.

Please fill out the following very quick survey so we can get a
headcount and begin planning appropriately:
https://www.surveymonkey.com/s/L32DWK6


We've received a couple of questions regarding the weekend:
- The retreat will officially kick off Friday, Oct 10 during the day,
and last until Sunday, mid-day.
- There will be a cost for attending the event - $150 in order to help
cover room and food. Once there, we hope to keep any other expenses
you'll incurr to a minimum, so you can enjoy the weekend to the
fullest.
- Scholarships will be addressed at a later date, once we are able to
confirm a budget and attendance.
- Significant others are invited - just make sure to let us know they're coming!

Thanks again, and we look forward to seeing you all in October!



2014 Planning Committee

Sam, Ernestine, Tariq, Joe, Ana, Bethany, Varun, Garrett, and Ansaf




--
Samantha A. Penabad
spenabad@gmail.com | (908) 962-7452

Thanks for your notes back after we announced October 10th as the
weekend for the 2014 CM Retreat - we share your excitement!

The retreat will be hosted in San Diego this year so we'll be able to
enjoy some great weather as well as the company of friends.

Please fill out the following very quick survey so we can get a
headcount and begin planning appropriately:
https://www.surveymonkey.com/s/L32DWK6


We've received a couple of questions regarding the weekend:
- The retreat will officially kick off Friday, Oct 10 during the day,
and last until Sunday, mid-day.
- There will be a cost for attending the event - $150 in order to help
cover room and food. Once there, we hope to keep any other expenses
you'll incurr to a minimum, so you can enjoy the weekend to the
fullest.
- Scholarships will be addressed at a later date, once we are able to
confirm a budget and attendance.
- Significant others are invited - just make sure to let us know they're coming!

Thanks again, and we look forward to seeing you all in October!



2014 Planning Committee

Sam, Ernestine, Tariq, Joe, Ana, Bethany, Varun, Garrett, and Ansaf




--
Samantha A. Penabad
spenabad@gmail.com | (908) 962-7452

Ok, sounds good.

I'll call up CTAdvantage tomorrow and inform them that they should direct payment inquiries for the E2E invoice to you at the 301 King St address. I'll also tell them that the KMD company is being shut down and because of this you're expecting to not have to pay for the representation fee for that company. Have you had a chance to write up a few sentences on what timeline/condition you'd like for the asset transfer contract?
